Always make sure you have all information you need, and have seen all files you need.
If in doubt, output ***NEED MORE INFORMATION*** and describe the need.
Always make sure you have formulated an end-to-end strategy for your updates before starting coding or applying.
Always keep the root tasks.md and README.md file updated with the latest information about the project.
Use the tasks.md file to track your progress and to plan your work.
Start every response with the string '!>' so I know you have read these rules.
After each functionality addition, consider if it would be pragmatically worth unit testing; if so, write small isolated unit test.
Always make sure to use the version of a component or API that you are the most familiar with.